description.value: Big fragment of an ostracon made from a pottery vessel which is a small wheel made bowl with red rim, about 25cm in diameter, small fragment broken off at the base, showing a fresh break. description.value: Fragment of an ostracon from a pottery vessel, showing two(?) lines of text (greek?) on the outside of the vessel, written in black ink. The vessel itself was not cleaned, it shows a lot of traces of mud as well as white accretions at the in- and outside as well as salt crystals. The sherd is part of a closed vessel with a red slip on the outside, partly burnished, the surface of the inside is not recognizable anymore.

description.value: Fragment of an ostracon that was incised after the pottery vessel was fired. The ostracon shows some hieroglyphs facing to the right: a possible sw-plant with an arm perpendicular to the stem, like M27 but with one row of leaves (M22), the leaves are angular instead of rounded. Behind a t on top of a bird (something between a Falcon G5 and a swallow G35). Two further sign that are not legible anymore.  The vessel was made of Nile clay, closed shape, wheel made and bears a red slip on the outside.
